latestIgtvVideos.caption:
“EK”
The concept originates from the traditional function of ‘Haldi’. This ritual also happens to be among one of the most loved pre-wedding rituals. As it is filled with fun & flare resulting in tons of beautiful memories to cherish. The campaign is reimagines the hues of kesar, mirch & haldi sold in ancient souks. Mixing these vibrant hues & sprinkled with chevron and floral prints. In the campaign there are 7 woman in different shapes, sizes & colours, were they are showing that we all different but we all are “EK”, irrespective of there colour, shape & size. They unite together as they are future of today, they are the real women. 👩🏻‍🤝‍👩🏽

latestIgtvVideos.title: KERRATO HAIR FIBRES
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys!
This might not be easy to believe for you all as I'm reviewing a product which I had never thought I would, After a thorough discussion with the brand about the product, understanding its pro's & con's (nothing as such). I gave a try to this product.
As most of you are aware that my forehead is big & my hair thin, and most of the time I keep my hair open so that my scalp isn’t visible because of my thin hairline.
So, I recently tried this product from @kerrato.in , and man! I'm so in love with this product. I can now tie my hair up, however, without even thinking about the thin hairline it leaves.

Kerrato hair fibres instantly makes your hair thick and adds volume. Kerrato hair fibres are made using 100% keratin and are suitable for people with thin hair, alopecia, male pattern baldness, female pattern baldness, hair loss.
Well I rate this product 4.5/5. As there is no side effect also its gives a natural look the entire day. It lasts till the date you shampoo your hair.

Say goodbye to visible scalp as with Kerrato Hair Fibre you can slay the whole day. 🥰

Available for best prices at www.kerrato.com, They are also available on Amazon and Flipkart. 🛒
